	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 19th 6:43 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=136182><span id=Scholar>MeddIng</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>128 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Dont bother to camp the janitor for the small pieces of HQ ore to make this sewing kit. Instead, head over to High Hold Keep and buy a large block of HQ ore (or 2, or 3...) and then head back to Rivervale. In the druid area, next to the non-vale forge, there is an NPC selling smithing supplies. Buy a chisel and put it into the forge with a large block of HQ ore (no water). It turns into a small block. Then repeat with the small block to make 2 small pieces of HQ ore. Its that simple! Then simply put the 2 pieces of HQ ore back into the forge with some water for the bits. The vale forge is over near the female wood elf bard. I made mine on the first attempt with a smithing skill of 110 (Ya, pure luck). Failed making a second one.<br><br>So, leave the poor janitor to his duties of cleaning up goblin and newbie guts off the floor and go make your own pieces.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
